      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) with documented V&V history; solution controls and convergence criteria logged per SOPs.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 is a commercially validated solver with published benchmark results. Internal SOP CFDQ-07 governs case setup, convergence monitoring (residuals < 1e-5, mass imbalance < 0.01 %), and output archiving. All simulation files version-controlled in Git repository tagged v3.1.2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, pipe flow) at Gradation 2 fidelity.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 code verification confirmed against ASME V&V 20 benchmark suite. Lid-driven cavity (Re = 1000) and fully developed pipe flow solutions match analytical references within 0.3 %. No custom UDFs employed that would require additional verification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5 % on primary QoI (RH index) using at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three hexahedral-dominant meshes generated: 3.1 M, 7.8 M, and 12.4 M cells (refinement ratio r = 1.59). GCI on RH index: 4.7 % (coarse-medium), 1.2 % (medium-fine). Asymptotic convergence ratio 0.94, confirming approach to grid-independent solution. Fine mesh (12.4 M) adopted for all production runs. Near-wall resolution y+ < 1 on impeller and volute surfaces."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) documented and replicated in CFD setup within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro test conditions documented in laboratory protocol LP-HEM-003. Inlet flow rates controlled to ±0.05 L/min; rotational speed to ±25 rpm; blood analogue (glycerol-water, μ = 3.5 mPa·s at 37 °C) characterised by rheometry. CFD boundary conditions set to nominal experimental values; sensitivity to ±5 % flow and ±50 rpm speed assessed via Monte Carlo."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or NMRSE) defined and evaluated against acceptance threshold for each validation QoI.",
      "rationale": "Normalised mean absolute error (NMAE) computed for RH index across 5 operating points: NMAE = 4.3 %, well below the 10 % acceptance threshold. H-Q curve maximum deviation 4.1 %. Wall shear stress RMS deviation 6.8 % against PIV reference. All metrics satisfy acceptance criteria defined in validation plan VP-CPB-2025."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validated QoIs (RH index, shear stress, pressure head) are directly mechanistically linked to the COU decision (worst-case hemolysis identification).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the regulatory acceptance metric for comparative hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Wall shear stress and pressure head are mechanistically coupled to RH through the power-law hemolysis model (Zhang et al. 2011). Validation of all three QoIs provides layered confidence that the CFD model correctly represents the hemolysis-generating physics relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the operating envelope (flow rates, speeds) and geometric configuration representative of COU conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry used in COU simulations. Operating points span 2–6 L/min and 2000–4000 rpm, bracketing all five COU operating conditions. Blood analogue fluid properties match clinical CPB range. Geometric similarity confirmed by coordinate measuring machine (CMM) inspection of acrylic replica (dimensional tolerance ±0.05 mm)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; commercial solver with documented validation history is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2, explicit numerical solver error quantification beyond GCI is not mandated. The use of ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 with documented benchmark performance and the discretization error assessment (GCI < 1.2 % on fine mesh) collectively provide adequate confidence in solver numerical accuracy for this COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst training records and SOP adherence are sufficient controls.",
      "rationale": "Analyst team holds CFD competency certification (internal program CFDC-L2). All simulations executed under SOP CFDQ-07 with mandatory peer review of case setup files prior to production runs. Independent checklist review completed by senior analyst (ID: SA-042). Formal use-error quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection justified by literature and sensitivity study.",
      "rationale": "k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on published performance for rotating machinery hemolysis CFD (Hariharan et al. 2015). Sensitivity study comparing k-ω SST vs. realizable k-ε showed < 3 % difference in RH index across all operating points, confirming model form uncertainty is not dominant. Formal model form error quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties, geometric parameters, and boundary conditions traceable to documented sources with stated uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (density 1050 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) sourced from rheometric measurements (report RHE-2024-11) with ±2 % uncertainty. Pump geometry from CAD file FDA-GCP-v2.stp, CMM-verified. Inlet velocity profile derived from Womersley solution for pulsatile flow; rotational speed from tachometer calibration (NIST-traceable, ±0.3 %). Power-law hemolysis model coefficients from Zhang et al. (2011) meta-analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
